            "prompt": "You are implementing Unit 8: Discovery Controller for the reme encrypted messenger.\n\n## Task\n\nCreate `apps/client/src/discovery/` module with a controller that:\n1. Subscribes to `broadcast::Receiver<DiscoveryEvent>` from a discovery backend\n2. For each `PeerDiscovered` event, decodes TXT records to extract routing key\n3. Matches routing key against known contacts (from storage)\n4. For matched contacts, verifies identity via HTTP challenge-response\n5. On successful verification, registers the peer as an ephemeral HTTP target via the coordinator\n6. On `PeerLost`, removes the corresponding target\n7. Handles repeated `PeerDiscovered` for the same `instance_name` as updates (address change)\n8. Caps tracked peers at 256\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\napps/client/src/discovery/\n├── mod.rs          — pub mod controller; re-exports\n└── controller.rs   — DiscoveryController struct and spawn logic\n```\n\n### DiscoveryController\n\n```rust\npub struct DiscoveryController {\n    /// Maps instance_name → (TargetId, Option<PublicID>)\n    /// Tracks which discovered peers have been registered as targets\n    peer_index: HashMap<String, PeerEntry>,\n    /// Maps routing_key → Vec<PublicID> for quick contact lookup\n    contact_index: HashMap<[u8; 16], Vec<PublicID>>,\n    /// Max tracked peers\n    max_peers: usize,\n}\n\nstruct PeerEntry {\n    target_id: TargetId,\n    verified_identity: Option<PublicID>,\n    addresses: Vec<IpAddr>,\n    port: u16,\n}\n```\n\n### spawn function\n\n```rust\npub fn spawn(\n    mut events: broadcast::Receiver<DiscoveryEvent>,\n    coordinator: Arc<TransportCoordinator>,\n    contacts: Vec<(PublicID, [u8; 16])>,  // (pubkey, routing_key) pairs\n    cancel: CancellationToken,\n) -> JoinHandle<()>\n```\n\nThe spawn function creates the controller, builds the contact_index, and runs an event loop:\n\n```rust\nloop {\n    tokio::select! {\n        () = cancel.cancelled() => break,\n        event = events.recv() => {\n  